**Event Title**: Health Care Hacking Community

**Organizers**: Brucifer and F3n1x

**Description**: 
- A gathering for conference attendees to learn and share information on healthcare cybersecurity and its relation to personal health.
- Aimed at promoting discussions on the hacking of healthcare devices.

**Details**:
- "Everything you need to know... More Details Coming Soon."
  
**Hours of Operation**:
- Monday: Expo Closed 
- Tuesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Wednesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Thursday: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- Friday: 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**Educational Focus**:
- How Health Care Devices are secured.
- Functionality of Health Care Devices.
- Interacting with Health Care Devices (HCDs).

**MiniBadge**: 
- A MiniBadge will be available; visit the booth for details.

**Desktop Wallpaper**: 
- Community desktop wallpaper available for download.

**Additional Resources**:
- Join online community on Discord.
- MiniBadge specifications and building tutorials available on GitHub and YouTube.

**Website**: [SAINTCON Health Care Hacking Community](https://saintcon.org/com-health-care-hacking-community/) 

**Date of Information**: October 2023